Package: zelig2
Title: Modern Statistical Modeling with Quantities of Interest
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Theodore", "Caputi", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "tcaputi@mit.edu")
Description: A modern reimplementation of the Zelig package (King, Tomz, and
    Wittenberg 2000) providing a unified workflow for statistical modeling:
    zelig2() -> setx() -> sim() -> plot(). Estimates models, sets
    counterfactual covariate scenarios, simulates quantities of interest
    (expected values, predicted values, first differences), and visualizes
    results. Supports fixed effects via 'fixest', survey weights via 'survey',
    robust/clustered/bootstrap standard errors via 'sandwich', and automatic
    handling of categorical variables.
